OL,2,R# {5j5 s{5z57            U'a|wk
OL,3,ETHE OPINIONATED PIGG``````````U`///{5n'
OL,4,                               U*~}|>
OL,5,B"Children are stupid, everyoneU8<;6
OL,6,Bknows that. So why get one to Um}e/!'
OL,7,Bpresent the games section on the       
OL,8,Bflagship show of BBC Television's youth
OL,9,Bprogramming?                           
OL,11,F"The boy - I can't remember his name - 
OL,12,Fhas a bad haircut which most probably  
OL,13,Fcauses viewers to turn off whenever his
OL,14,Fover-smiley little face appears on     
OL,15,Fscreen. Who can respect the opinions of
OL,16,Fa six-year-old with puffy hair?        
OL,17,FCertainly not anyone older than him."  
