OL,2,R# {5j5 s{5z57            U'a|wk
OL,3,ETHE OPINIONATED PIGG``````````U`///{5n'
OL,4,                               U*~}|>
OL,5,B"It's the age-old problem -   U8<;6
OL,6,BTV show producers still think Um}e/!'
OL,7,Bvideo games are the domain of sweaty,  
OL,8,Bafter-school-computer-club members,    
OL,9,Bwhen in reality they've evolved far    
OL,10,Bbeyond that.                           
OL,12,F"Why can't gamesplayers be treated with
OL,13,Fa little respect? The BBC's music      
OL,14,Foutput isn't presented by              
OL,15,Fpre-pubescents with whiny voices, and  
OL,16,FI'd bet that the demographics of       
OL,17,Fgamesplayers and music listeners are   
OL,18,Ffar closer than the BBC suspect."      
OL,19,B                                       
